  "prompt": "How do I search if any of my friends and relatives are here on Quora?",
  "response": "To search for friends and relatives on Quora, you can follow these steps:\n\n1. **Search by Name:**\n   - Use the search bar at the top of the Quora homepage.\n   - Type in the name of your friend or relative and press Enter.\n   - Look through the search results to see if you can find their profile.\n\n2. **Sync Contacts:**\n   - Quora may offer an option to sync your contacts from your email account.\n   - Go to your settings or profile options and find the feature to sync contacts.\n   - Follow the instructions to sync your contacts, which may help you find people you know who are already on Quora.\n\n3. **Social Media Connections:**\n   - If you have linked your Quora account with your social media accounts (like Facebook), you might be able to find friends who are also connected through those platforms.\n   - Check the \"People You May Know\" section or similar suggestions that Quora provides based on your linked accounts.\n\n4. **Browsing Topics:**\n   - If you know their interests or expertise, browse topics they might be following or contributing to.\n   - You can find users who are active in specific topics and check if any familiar names appear.\n\nRemember to respect privacy and only search for people you have a legitimate connection with.",
